<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="ADA02" sex="1"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><roleName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Robert</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Adair</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1763-05-24"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1855-10-03"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">politician</occupation><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">diplomatist</occupation><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Adair was a close friend of <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="FOX01">Charles James Fox</persName>. He sat in parliament 1799-1812 but was
    primarily known for his extensive 
    travel and diplomatic activity for which he was awarded GCB in 1831.</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Godwin notes meeting a W J Adair in 1789, and the early Adairs in the diary are linked to circles around <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="HOL02">Brand Hollis</persName>,
    although there is no Adair between May 1790 and the appearance of R Adair in 1796. After the
    first R Adair mention in 1796 the use of the name with the initial is frequent, but there are also
    entries where there is no initial and where the circles (especially <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="DEB01">Debrett's</persName>) are
    indistinguishable from those within which he meets R Adair. It is possible that Godwin had
    consistently distinguished R Adair from another Adair, whom we are unable to identify, but it
    is also possible, and the context of the meetings in the diary make it likely, that Adair and R
    Adair are used interchangeably from 1796.  The entries have been coded accordingly.  This is bolstered by the fact that 
   <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="ROB03">Henry Crabb Robinson</persName> notes the presence of 
    'Adair the diplomatist' at a dinner on 18 Oct 1813. </p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">In addition, R Adair appears in the 1796 lists, under 1796.</p></note><bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="other"><title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">DNB</title></bibl><bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="printedbook"><title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">The Diary of Henry Crabb Robinson</title>, ed. by Edith J. Morley, 3 vols (London: J.M. Dent and Sons, 1938)</bibl><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="appearancesInDiary"><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1788"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1789"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1790"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1791"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1792"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1793"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1794"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1795"/><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1796"><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-04-16" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-04-28" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-05-07" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-05-10" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-09-01" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1796-10-04" n="notVenue" type="ah"/></ab><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1797"><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1797-01-09" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1797-03-18" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1797-05-08" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1797-06-01" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1797-06-02" n="notVenue" type="ah"/></a